pros:
- High-quality individuals, fun to work with and interact with;
- As this position was tied to being a student, it was made to be very versatile in taking days off/slashing the work hours when needed.
- Pretty fun day-to-day tasks, especially if you like problem-solving;
- Normal workload.

cons:
- The pay is not the best and sorta devalues the importance of the customer-focused work that is being done;
- As previously stated this position is tied to being a student so naturally, you will lose your job once you graduate/quit university;
- At least from personal experience it is seemingly hard to progress and advance to another position in the company, however, the possibilities are still there.

pros:
- Awesome team and really positive work environment;
- Free lunch everyday;
- Possibility to work from home 2 days a week;
- Travels!
